What insurance is suitable for me?
The insurance of a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident is a significant expenditure which depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
The choice of suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we're talking about.
Insurance of the vehicle is an agreement between the insurance undertaking and the insurance undertaking.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking will receive an agreed insurance amount at a certain amount for taking over the damage to the insurance undertaking in the event of an accident.
Insurance is the price of insurance which is determined by reference to various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of driver's licence, type of vehicle insured or its use etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the more likely the accident occurs, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both persons aged 25 and women must pay lower insurance premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that persons living in marriage had fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journey, and the likelihood of an accident.
The increase in frequency of driving increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurers consider when determining the insurance price.
Therefore, the driver must study well the situation in order to choose such insurance as is best suited to his insurance profile.
We will show here the most important variable for the choice of the type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 are faced with various disadvantages such as little driving experience and short driving licence holding when they want to negotiate insurance at an affordable price.
Although the ideal for good cover is insurance against all risks, there are even cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all insurance risks with a discount in order to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would provide for the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"Part of the remuneration of the insurance event provided by the client will be determined in advance in determining the insurance price which will be higher than the level of participation," explains Luis Noguera, Chief of First Europe in Spain, Internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other operators by ensuring that the client is insured against damage caused to other persons, but not against the damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A recommendation.
If you're under twenty-five years old, try to be careful and prevent accidents as far as possible, because it will affect your bonus and make it possible to reduce future insurance.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
On the contrary, the small amount is the increase in the mentioned base rate.
"The bonus and the small will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to raise the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the limit of twenty-five years, it makes it easier for drivers to negotiate insurance because the customer risk index is decreasing, thanks to experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to negotiate insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people usually cannot draw on the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident and even in the course of the proceedings," he assures the director of the European company in Spain and adds that most accidents occur in the second year of the proceedings, when he has already been overcome by "the fear of a rookie".
However, if the client is married, but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange for insurance against all risks if, however, his economic situation permits.
Families with children are considered to be the lowest risk index clientele and therefore their accruals will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium (which could be EUR 300) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting at the third year of purchase of the vehicle.
"their management is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford to get the highest discount," said Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended to insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which is EUR 150) or insurance extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents considerable expenditure, which is a good reason for properly examining the insurance options that would suit us most in terms of our personal situation.
