But the flattened greenhouse effect caused by carbon dioxide, the atmospheric erosion of solar radiation and the lower speed of rotation sent Venus on a completely different development path.
Today, a planet without water, the temperature on the surface is quite hot for the melting of lead, and the storm and the winds of the hurricane are raging.
